1
00:01:46,240 --> 00:01:48,470
Twenty questions. Go.

2
00:01:51,411 --> 00:01:53,902
You're a man. Are you in politics?

3
00:01:58,519 --> 00:02:00,783
Warm beer. Tastes like piss.

4
00:02:09,830 --> 00:02:11,627
It's your turn, babe.

5
00:02:12,132 --> 00:02:13,622
Dead or alive?

6
00:02:14,401 --> 00:02:18,098
Don't you think that's
a really stupid question these days?

7
00:02:19,940 --> 00:02:21,874
You know, he's kind of an asshole,

8
00:02:21,942 --> 00:02:23,773
but if you need me
to take care of him, I will.

9
00:02:23,844 --> 00:02:24,868
I can hear you.

10
00:02:24,945 --> 00:02:27,607
He's the one in the family
with all the brains.

11
00:02:27,681 --> 00:02:29,171
Is that right?

12
00:02:36,890 --> 00:02:39,051
All right, the interstate's coming up.
What do we do?

13
00:02:39,126 --> 00:02:41,492
Don't get on it. Stay on this back road.

14
00:02:41,562 --> 00:02:43,052
How come every time you say that,

15
00:02:43,130 --> 00:02:46,065
we end up in a three-hour scenic tour
in the middle of nowhere?

16
00:02:46,133 --> 00:02:47,725
Look, we agreed on the rules, didn't we?

17
00:02:47,801 --> 00:02:49,894
And by taking it, we're breaking what?

18
00:02:49,970 --> 00:02:52,564
The rule that says
we shouldn't take the interstate.

19
00:02:52,639 --> 00:02:56,803
"I guess we wouldn't want
to break any rules," he said,

20
00:02:56,877 --> 00:02:59,311
drinking his beer
as he drove the stolen Mercedes

21
00:02:59,379 --> 00:03:03,042
ridiculously over the speed limit,
and, look, no hands!

22
00:03:03,183 --> 00:03:04,912
- Babe, don't!
- Stop!

23
00:03:05,752 --> 00:03:07,652
- Stop it, you moron!
- Don't!

24
00:03:14,795 --> 00:03:19,926
- All right, smartass, I'll read the map.
- Can you? It has actual writing on it.

25
00:03:20,934 --> 00:03:22,299
Very funny.

26
00:03:25,272 --> 00:03:27,001
Hey, hey, hey, hey!

27
00:03:35,682 --> 00:03:37,013
Hey, guys.

28
00:03:37,985 --> 00:03:40,215
All right, windows, everybody.

29
00:03:43,423 --> 00:03:45,755
What the hell is this guy doing?

30
00:03:46,960 --> 00:03:49,554
My daughter and I, we ran out of gas.

31
00:03:51,531 --> 00:03:54,500
All right, sir,
please move your car out of the road.

32
00:03:54,568 --> 00:03:58,902
We left Denver yesterday morning.
Last gas we got was Colorado Springs.

33
00:03:59,539 --> 00:04:02,133
I'm sorry, we can't help you.
Now move your car!

34
00:04:02,209 --> 00:04:03,733
Look, all we need
is just a little bit of gas.

35
00:04:03,810 --> 00:04:05,437
Yeah, I'm sure you do.
You and everybody else.

36
00:04:05,512 --> 00:04:07,241
Stay where you are!

37
00:04:07,347 --> 00:04:10,407
We can trade you for it.
We got food and water.

38
00:04:10,484 --> 00:04:13,510
- Brian, we have more than enough.
- More than... How do you know that?

39
00:04:13,587 --> 00:04:16,818
- I said do not get any closer!
- Brian, he looks clean.

40
00:04:16,890 --> 00:04:18,881
Or he could be incubating.
Think about it for a second...

41
00:04:18,959 --> 00:04:21,018
Guys! She's got it.

42
00:04:21,495 --> 00:04:22,587
Shit!

43
00:04:24,064 --> 00:04:26,259
Come on, come on, come on...

44
00:04:43,450 --> 00:04:45,315
They'll die out there.

45
00:04:46,353 --> 00:04:47,843
Everyone dies.

46
00:04:55,595 --> 00:04:59,429
<i>The rules are simple.</i>
<i>At least, that's how my brother sees it.</i>

47
00:05:00,701 --> 00:05:03,761
<i>One, avoid the infected at all costs.</i>

48
00:05:04,237 --> 00:05:06,671
<i>Their breath is highly contagious.</i>

49
00:05:07,407 --> 00:05:11,537
<i>Two, disinfect anything they've touched</i>
<i>in the last 24 hours.</i>

50
00:05:12,345 --> 00:05:16,509
<i>Three, the sick are already dead.</i>
<i>They can't be saved.</i>

51
00:05:17,818 --> 00:05:19,342
<i>You break the rules, you die.</i>

52
00:05:20,420 --> 00:05:22,786
<i>You follow them, you live.</i>

53
00:05:23,824 --> 00:05:24,984
<i>Maybe.</i>

54
00:05:46,346 --> 00:05:48,246
Hey. Look what I found.

55
00:05:50,684 --> 00:05:51,810
Great.

56
00:05:51,885 --> 00:05:56,151
Hey, if you happen to find a brand-new
factory-issued oil pan, holler.

57
00:06:02,062 --> 00:06:05,896
- Are you sure you can't fix it?
- It's blown, lvy Boy.

58
00:06:14,708 --> 00:06:16,539
- Brian.
- What?

59
00:06:19,813 --> 00:06:21,940
All that car needed was gas.

60
00:06:22,783 --> 00:06:26,241
Wait, what? No. No, no, no way.

61
00:06:27,053 --> 00:06:30,284
- Lf we sit here, we're just gonna die.
- We won't if we go back?

62
00:06:30,357 --> 00:06:33,758
You saw the girl.
You saw the blood, the rashes.

63
00:06:35,095 --> 00:06:36,926
Bobby, come on, you saw her.

64
00:06:36,997 --> 00:06:39,295
- Am I the only one here?
- Kate, we do not have a lot of options...

65
00:06:39,366 --> 00:06:40,594
They're your rules!

66
00:06:40,667 --> 00:06:42,828
Danny, tell your girlfriend
to get her shit together.

67
00:06:42,903 --> 00:06:46,100
- I'm not his girlfriend.
- She's not my girlfriend.

68
00:06:47,641 --> 00:06:51,338
All right, then tell me, tell me.
Why the hell is she here?

69
00:06:53,280 --> 00:06:55,646
Why didn't we let her sit tight
in her McMansion,

70
00:06:55,715 --> 00:06:57,114
- waiting for the looters?
- Okay.

71
00:06:57,184 --> 00:07:01,416
Could we just calm down and try
and think this thing through? Please.

72
00:07:02,455 --> 00:07:05,117
- Yeah.
- So what about the car?

73
00:07:07,527 --> 00:07:09,051
I don't know, Danny. I'm trying to think.

74
00:07:09,129 --> 00:07:11,825
- Well, we need that car...
- I know that!

75
00:07:15,769 --> 00:07:16,861
Shit!

76
00:07:32,786 --> 00:07:35,277
All right, put your masks on, guys.

77
00:07:49,703 --> 00:07:51,227
Frank Holloway.

78
00:07:55,141 --> 00:07:57,166
We're gonna need your car.

79
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:02,471
Yeah, I figured as much.

80
00:08:05,819 --> 00:08:08,720
Do you really want to splatter
your brand-new vehicle

81
00:08:08,788 --> 00:08:13,191
with the insides of someone who,
for all you know, may be infected?

82
00:08:14,160 --> 00:08:16,060
We got loads of Clorox.

83
00:08:17,297 --> 00:08:19,265
- Cleanup is not my chief concern.
- Brian, that's all right.

84
00:08:19,332 --> 00:08:21,596
- That's close enough.
- I picked up a radio transmission

85
00:08:21,668 --> 00:08:24,660
from a school outside of Farmington
last week.

86
00:08:24,905 --> 00:08:27,135
People from all over the state
are traveling there.

87
00:08:27,207 --> 00:08:28,469
For what?

88
00:08:28,875 --> 00:08:31,605
The CDC, they set up some kind
of emergency response center.

89
00:08:31,678 --> 00:08:33,646
They've got a new serum.

90
00:08:33,847 --> 00:08:36,941
That's one hell of a story, man.
I don't think I've heard that one yet.

91
00:08:37,017 --> 00:08:38,143
Are they getting results?

92
00:08:38,218 --> 00:08:40,118
No, they're not getting any results, Kate.

93
00:08:40,186 --> 00:08:44,247
They've got a new treatment, and I am
taking my daughter there in this car.

94
00:08:44,324 --> 00:08:47,521
Now, if you're onboard with that, great.
If not...

95
00:08:47,961 --> 00:08:50,555
This is a fairytale, and he knows it.

96
00:08:51,631 --> 00:08:53,223
It's the Baltimore vaccine all over again.

97
00:08:53,300 --> 00:08:54,927
It's a bunch of retrovirals
that don't work for shit.

98
00:08:55,001 --> 00:08:56,764
So go ahead, Brian.
Shoot him in the head.

99
00:08:56,836 --> 00:08:58,326
Wait! Hey.

100
00:09:02,042 --> 00:09:03,532
I got an idea.

101
00:09:31,771 --> 00:09:32,829
Hey.

102
00:09:34,074 --> 00:09:37,009
Want to know a secret? About boys?

103
00:09:38,411 --> 00:09:40,936
Their bark is worse than their bite.

104
00:09:41,314 --> 00:09:43,339
- You know what I mean?
- No.

105
00:09:43,416 --> 00:09:46,112
- It's okay.
- Don't listen to her, kiddo.

106
00:09:46,453 --> 00:09:50,514
- Trust me, she loves it when I bite.
- Why don't you eat me, Brian?

107
00:09:50,590 --> 00:09:54,549
- I think we can arrange that.
- Jesus, Brian! She's, like, eight.

108
00:09:54,995 --> 00:09:57,395
Yeah, well, mentally, so is he.

109
00:10:27,060 --> 00:10:30,655
<i>Adiós,</i> Road Warrior.
You crap piece of shit.

110
00:10:34,701 --> 00:10:36,896
<i>But Godless governments have fallen,</i>

111
00:10:36,970 --> 00:10:39,165
<i>and the armies of man</i>
<i>have perished by his hand...</i>

112
00:10:39,239 --> 00:10:40,638
Pattycake, pattycake...

113
00:10:40,707 --> 00:10:45,872
<i>... for this pandemic is the flail of God</i>
<i>and the world his threshing floor,</i>

114
00:10:45,945 --> 00:10:48,971
<i>and, implacably,</i>
<i>he will thresh out his harvest</i>

115
00:10:49,049 --> 00:10:53,611
<i>until the wheat is separated from</i>
<i>the chaff, the righteous from the sinner.</i>

116
00:10:53,887 --> 00:10:58,347
<i>And make no mistake about it,</i>
<i>there shall be far more chaff than wheat.</i>

117
00:10:59,225 --> 00:11:00,249
<i>Few chosen...</i>

118
00:11:00,326 --> 00:11:04,057
Come to think of it,
I haven't seen much weed around lately.

119
00:11:05,665 --> 00:11:08,429
- Very funny.
- What?

120
00:11:11,171 --> 00:11:13,071
Just show some respect.

121
00:11:13,139 --> 00:11:15,972
For what?
That God's punishing my daughter?

122
00:11:16,776 --> 00:11:19,210
Who's he rewarding? Who, you?

123
00:11:19,913 --> 00:11:22,677
- That's not what I'm saying.
- What are you saying?

124
00:11:22,749 --> 00:11:24,910
Some people locked themselves away,
piled up food,

125
00:11:24,984 --> 00:11:28,283
didn't even pick up the phone.
They were dead in a week.

126
00:11:28,354 --> 00:11:30,379
Me, I worked at the stadium,
digging those mass graves for 400...

127
00:11:30,457 --> 00:11:33,153
- 400 bucks a day!
- That's exactly right.

128
00:11:33,660 --> 00:11:36,322
You can laugh all you want,
but I was up to my knees in that shit,

129
00:11:36,396 --> 00:11:37,556
and here I am.

130
00:11:37,630 --> 00:11:41,225
So you're immune or chosen
or something?

131
00:11:42,035 --> 00:11:44,026
I'm here and they're not.

132
00:11:45,305 --> 00:11:47,637
So, then, I guess you won't mind
kissing my daughter good night for me,

133
00:11:47,707 --> 00:11:49,072
huh, Brian?

134
00:11:51,344 --> 00:11:53,005
I didn't think so.

135
00:11:57,717 --> 00:11:59,947
So much for being chosen, huh?

136
00:12:01,087 --> 00:12:03,578
That's hysterical, huh, lvy League?

137
00:12:06,626 --> 00:12:08,321
Where'd you go to school, Danny?

138
00:12:08,394 --> 00:12:11,227
- He got a scholarship to go to Harvard.
- Yale.

139
00:12:11,297 --> 00:12:14,391
- It was Yale, actually.
- It doesn't really matter, does it?

140
00:12:14,467 --> 00:12:18,597
A little something shut the place down
before freshman orientation.

141
00:12:19,372 --> 00:12:22,773
- Watch it, Brian.
- How's that for a knee-slapper?

142
00:12:23,276 --> 00:12:26,074
- Why do you have to be such a dick?
- Come on!

143
00:12:26,146 --> 00:12:27,943
Watch out! Watch out!

144
00:12:43,062 --> 00:12:45,121
You! You stay in the back, you hear me?

145
00:12:45,198 --> 00:12:47,962
Hey, I will if you keep your eyes
on the goddamn road!

146
00:12:48,034 --> 00:12:50,730
Hey, you can get out anytime!
You can get out right now!

147
00:12:50,803 --> 00:12:55,467
- Okay. Okay. Okay.
- Kate! Kate!

148
00:12:56,576 --> 00:12:59,670
The tape held.
You don't have to worry about it.

149
00:13:01,147 --> 00:13:04,480
Are you okay? What is it?

150
00:13:11,324 --> 00:13:14,157
Damn it.
I think she knocked a filling loose.

151
00:13:14,227 --> 00:13:15,751
I weep for you.

152
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:22,199
It's locked.

153
00:13:31,077 --> 00:13:32,738
Danny, be careful.

154
00:13:33,947 --> 00:13:35,278
It's okay.

155
00:13:45,625 --> 00:13:46,717
Shit.

156
00:14:03,876 --> 00:14:06,140
Hey, are you all right? Danny!

157
00:14:07,213 --> 00:14:08,373
What happened?

158
00:14:12,685 --> 00:14:13,845
Jesus!

159
00:14:15,021 --> 00:14:17,251
Just get the gas and let's go.

160
00:14:32,739 --> 00:14:35,537
Hey, kids, we'll be back in 20.

161
00:14:36,109 --> 00:14:38,805
Yeah, we'll be back in more like five.

162
00:14:40,113 --> 00:14:41,205
Shit.

163
00:14:42,081 --> 00:14:44,106
Bobby! Baby?

164
00:14:45,251 --> 00:14:48,243
- What's that?
- That?

165
00:14:49,722 --> 00:14:52,748
Well, Brian and I,

166
00:14:53,760 --> 00:14:57,127
we had a dad, too.
He was just like yours.

167
00:14:58,197 --> 00:15:02,361
And every summer, when we were little,
he would take us to this place.

168
00:15:02,435 --> 00:15:04,096
It's Turtle Beach.

169
00:15:04,470 --> 00:15:09,908
And we could swim and surf,
and we'd fish

170
00:15:10,777 --> 00:15:15,009
<i>and eat these soft-shell crab</i>
<i>sandwiches that were soaked in mayo.</i>

171
00:15:18,618 --> 00:15:20,677
Were there lots of turtles?

172
00:15:20,753 --> 00:15:24,814
Lots? God, there were thousands
of them! They were everywhere.

173
00:15:25,258 --> 00:15:29,490
<i>I mean, you could barely put your foot</i>
<i>in the water without stepping on one.</i>

174
00:15:29,562 --> 00:15:32,861
Sometimes they'd be stacked up
on top of each other.

175
00:15:33,066 --> 00:15:36,331
- That's impossible!
- It is possible.

176
00:15:37,270 --> 00:15:41,229
- They were everywhere.
- Can we go to Turtle Beach with them?

177
00:15:42,642 --> 00:15:44,132
Time to sleep.

178
00:15:45,978 --> 00:15:49,072
What makes you think
you're gonna be safe there?

179
00:15:50,583 --> 00:15:52,312
It's an old motel.

180
00:15:53,286 --> 00:15:57,450
The place has been abandoned
for years. We'll go on scavenging trips

181
00:15:57,523 --> 00:16:01,015
and quarantine ourselves
every single time we get back,

182
00:16:01,427 --> 00:16:04,055
- and wait.
- Until they come for us.

183
00:16:05,164 --> 00:16:08,065
Until... Until the disease dies off.

184
00:16:09,202 --> 00:16:11,227
The disease or the people?

185
00:16:13,806 --> 00:16:15,933
It's the same thing, really.

186
00:16:19,145 --> 00:16:20,840
<i>Bobby, I love you,</i>

187
00:16:21,114 --> 00:16:24,277
and you know
what a dipshit I can be sometimes...

188
00:16:25,785 --> 00:16:27,548
What's the big deal?

189
00:16:30,623 --> 00:16:33,114
I think we should see other people.

190
00:16:36,596 --> 00:16:38,689
If that's the way you feel.

191
00:16:39,699 --> 00:16:41,496
It is the way I feel.

192
00:16:48,341 --> 00:16:51,333
- You can be such a dipshit sometimes.
- I know!

193
00:16:51,944 --> 00:16:55,038
Probably the biggest in the world
at this point.

194
00:17:17,003 --> 00:17:19,028
Do you ever think of Yale?

195
00:17:22,108 --> 00:17:24,076
Yeah. Sure.

196
00:17:26,212 --> 00:17:30,273
That, and all those things
you think you'll get to do someday.

197
00:17:37,190 --> 00:17:38,350
Jesus!

198
00:17:39,258 --> 00:17:42,523
- Put it out! Put the fire out!
- Go, go, go, go, go!

199
00:17:44,497 --> 00:17:47,091
Where do you think you're going, boy?

200
00:17:47,467 --> 00:17:48,900
- Hurry up.
- Hurry.

201
00:17:48,968 --> 00:17:51,869
Just keep it down. Keep it down.
Put it out.

202
00:19:56,262 --> 00:19:58,662
- Okay, I'll be right back.
- Daddy.

203
00:19:58,764 --> 00:20:00,561
Honey, I'm just going in there

204
00:20:00,633 --> 00:20:02,294
to make sure
there are no monsters under the bed.

205
00:20:02,368 --> 00:20:05,098
If there are monsters, you shouldn't go.

206
00:20:05,237 --> 00:20:08,832
Okay, now listen to me.
There's no reason to worry. All right?

207
00:20:08,908 --> 00:20:10,603
I'll be back before you can say
Captain Feathersword.

208
00:20:10,676 --> 00:20:12,473
Captain Feathersword.

209
00:20:13,746 --> 00:20:15,873
You're too smart for me, you know that?

210
00:20:15,948 --> 00:20:17,677
I'll stay with her.

211
00:20:18,951 --> 00:20:20,111
Bobby.

212
00:20:20,820 --> 00:20:22,788
Look, now is not the time, okay?

213
00:20:22,855 --> 00:20:26,052
The girls need some alone time
to talk about boys.

214
00:20:30,329 --> 00:20:33,127
I am serious.
Do not get too close to her.

215
00:20:33,332 --> 00:20:37,735
I'm serious. Just go. It's gonna be fine.

216
00:20:40,940 --> 00:20:44,171
You know, you are always doing
whatever the hell you want.

217
00:20:44,243 --> 00:20:46,143
That's why you love me!

218
00:21:04,230 --> 00:21:05,390
Hello?

219
00:21:09,335 --> 00:21:10,495
Hello?

220
00:21:48,708 --> 00:21:52,007
Looks like your hospital
ran out of patients, Frank.

221
00:21:55,681 --> 00:21:57,979
Come on. Let's get out of here.

222
00:22:02,922 --> 00:22:04,389
Where's Kate?

223
00:22:08,861 --> 00:22:10,852
- What is she doing?
- Kate?

224
00:22:11,831 --> 00:22:14,459
- We have to go. There's nothing here.
- You don't know that.

225
00:22:14,533 --> 00:22:16,330
Kate, they failed. Let's go.

226
00:22:16,402 --> 00:22:19,303
There's a whole wing
we haven't checked yet.

227
00:22:20,673 --> 00:22:22,971
You see? There are people here.

228
00:22:23,609 --> 00:22:24,701
Wait!

229
00:22:44,063 --> 00:22:45,462
No way.

230
00:22:46,932 --> 00:22:48,900
Oh, my God. They did it.

231
00:23:04,016 --> 00:23:06,780
- Sir. Sir!
- Yes?

232
00:23:09,388 --> 00:23:13,757
- Are you in charge here?
- No, you want Dr. Lindus.

233
00:23:14,093 --> 00:23:17,392
His office is on the second floor
of the old math building.

234
00:23:17,463 --> 00:23:20,660
But you won't find him there.
He died on Thursday.

235
00:23:21,967 --> 00:23:23,400
Doctor, we've come all the way
from Colorado.

236
00:23:23,469 --> 00:23:24,697
We heard that you had a serum here.

237
00:23:24,770 --> 00:23:28,536
It's my daughter, she's...
My daughter is very sick.

238
00:23:31,544 --> 00:23:33,876
- How long?
