Yeah, we'll just wave politely
and ask for help.

517
00:57:37,454 --> 00:57:39,479
Brian. Brian!

518
00:57:54,171 --> 00:57:57,538
Hey! I'll deal with this.

519
00:58:04,915 --> 00:58:07,315
- Stay where you are!
- Don't come any closer!

520
00:58:07,384 --> 00:58:11,718
I'm gonna stay right here.
We just need some gas.

521
00:58:12,923 --> 00:58:17,860
- Sorry. We don't have any to spare.
- I know. I understand.

522
00:58:21,632 --> 00:58:24,658
But I was just hoping
that maybe as a fellow Christian,

523
00:58:24,735 --> 00:58:28,102
- you might be able to help us.
- Please don't do that.

524
00:58:29,206 --> 00:58:32,334
You see, my wife in the car,
she's pregnant.

525
00:58:33,243 --> 00:58:36,610
We're just looking for a cool place
to have the baby,

526
00:58:36,980 --> 00:58:40,711
- see this thing through.
- Go in reverse. Let's go. Let's go.

527
00:58:40,884 --> 00:58:42,215
Good luck.

528
00:58:42,886 --> 00:58:44,410
- Go, go, go.
- Ma'am.

529
00:58:44,488 --> 00:58:46,353
- No, I can't.
- Please.

530
00:58:46,423 --> 00:58:48,015
I'm begging you!

531
00:58:50,928 --> 00:58:52,259
No, Brian!

532
00:58:56,934 --> 00:58:58,162
Get out!

533
00:59:00,304 --> 00:59:01,532
Get out!

534
00:59:40,377 --> 00:59:41,776
Get the gas.

535
00:59:43,814 --> 00:59:44,906
Oh, God.

536
00:59:57,127 --> 00:59:58,822
What are you doing?

537
00:59:58,895 --> 01:00:01,625
They weren't gonna give it to us, Danny.

538
01:00:02,432 --> 01:00:03,899
Help her out.

539
01:00:07,270 --> 01:00:11,536
You don't talk to me. You hear me?
You don't tell me what to do!

540
01:00:12,809 --> 01:00:16,768
Don't walk away from me,
you son of a bitch! I'm talking to you!

541
01:00:17,614 --> 01:00:20,082
- What the...
- I am talking to you,

542
01:00:20,250 --> 01:00:23,777
and I'm telling you what to do,
you self-righteous shit!

543
01:00:24,254 --> 01:00:26,916
It must be nice sitting on the sidelines

544
01:00:26,990 --> 01:00:28,958
while your dumb brother
wades in shit for you.

545
01:00:29,026 --> 01:00:31,256
- No, I don't...
- Somebody had to do it.

546
01:00:31,328 --> 01:00:32,989
- Was it gonna be you, Danny?
- You didn't have to...

547
01:00:33,063 --> 01:00:35,759
You remember...
You remember our last day at home?

548
01:00:36,166 --> 01:00:39,727
It wasn't you who went up to Mom
and Dad's room to get his gun, was it?

549
01:00:39,803 --> 01:00:43,500
It wasn't you! It wasn't you
who had to go up there and lie

550
01:00:43,573 --> 01:00:47,134
and tell them not to worry,
that you'd be back real soon.

551
01:00:47,477 --> 01:00:50,878
- They were alive? Alive?
- You knew they were.

552
01:00:51,448 --> 01:00:55,179
They were? You... You told me...

553
01:00:55,252 --> 01:01:00,519
- What you wanted to hear.
- You asshole! Asshole!

554
01:01:03,126 --> 01:01:05,651
Come here. Come here.
I'm an asshole for what?

555
01:01:05,729 --> 01:01:07,356
Tell me, Danny, asshole for what?

556
01:01:07,464 --> 01:01:08,726
For what?

557
01:01:08,999 --> 01:01:12,093
For letting you walk by
with a clean conscience?

558
01:01:14,004 --> 01:01:16,438
Well, that's what you like, Danny.

559
01:01:18,442 --> 01:01:19,966
Remember Bobby?

560
01:01:22,412 --> 01:01:24,141
You remember Bobby?

561
01:01:24,748 --> 01:01:26,807
I was the one that had to drag her
out of the car

562
01:01:26,883 --> 01:01:30,341
while you just sat there
watching me do it!

563
01:01:38,929 --> 01:01:40,521
Bobby was right.

564
01:01:43,600 --> 01:01:45,500
You got all the brains.

565
01:03:23,400 --> 01:03:24,560
<i>Danny.</i>

566
01:03:32,275 --> 01:03:34,266
Hey. Brian.

567
01:03:39,449 --> 01:03:40,780
Stop here.

568
01:03:43,386 --> 01:03:44,978
Brian. Brian.

569
01:03:45,722 --> 01:03:46,848
We're gonna stop at this house, okay?

570
01:03:46,923 --> 01:03:50,222
We're gonna find something
to dress your wound with.

571
01:03:50,360 --> 01:03:52,225
Whatever you say, Doc.

572
01:04:21,825 --> 01:04:24,521
Danny. There.

573
01:04:34,938 --> 01:04:36,803
A little closer.

574
01:04:37,807 --> 01:04:39,707
Keep going. Okay, stop.

575
01:05:15,679 --> 01:05:16,839
Hello?

576
01:05:36,666 --> 01:05:37,826
Hello!

577
01:05:41,571 --> 01:05:44,768
If you can hear me,
we just need medical supplies.

578
01:05:48,578 --> 01:05:50,102
Someone's hurt.

579
01:05:54,884 --> 01:05:56,545
We're not infected,

580
01:05:59,022 --> 01:06:01,320
and we don't mean you any harm.

581
01:06:02,459 --> 01:06:03,687
We're...

582
01:06:04,728 --> 01:06:08,755
We're just gonna take what we need,
and we'll leave.

583
01:07:32,549 --> 01:07:35,347
What happened? Oh, shit!
What's on you?

584
01:07:42,258 --> 01:07:45,125
It's not contagious. It's not human blood.

585
01:07:47,730 --> 01:07:49,288
It's dog blood.

586
01:07:52,669 --> 01:07:55,763
- You had me worried, little brother.
- I'm sorry.

587
01:07:58,341 --> 01:07:59,330
Sorry.

588
01:08:05,248 --> 01:08:10,481
Hey, don't take this the wrong way.
Can you pull down your pants?

589
01:08:40,283 --> 01:08:43,081
Hey, so much for being chosen, huh?

590
01:08:47,891 --> 01:08:49,222
I'm sorry.

591
01:09:20,757 --> 01:09:22,725
He's got it, doesn't he?

592
01:09:28,598 --> 01:09:29,690
Shit!

593
01:09:34,637 --> 01:09:38,368
<i>I don't know if there's anybody listening,</i>

594
01:09:39,676 --> 01:09:41,940
<i>but my generator is dying.</i>

595
01:09:42,879 --> 01:09:47,441
<i>So, if there is someone out there,</i>
<i>this is my last song.</i>

596
01:09:48,484 --> 01:09:52,477
<i>This is Laura Merkin,</i>
<i>last survivor of Corpus Christi, Texas,</i>

597
01:09:53,156 --> 01:09:55,386
<i>saying goodbye.</i>

598
01:10:11,608 --> 01:10:13,200
Can I see those?

599
01:10:38,201 --> 01:10:42,001
Bobby had this crazy idea.

600
01:10:45,308 --> 01:10:47,208
She wanted to be a mom.

601
01:10:51,547 --> 01:10:53,344
Can you believe that?

602
01:10:55,518 --> 01:10:56,746
Why not?

603
01:10:59,389 --> 01:11:00,617
With me?

604
01:11:04,694 --> 01:11:07,788
There are some things
I'm just not good at, man.

605
01:11:11,668 --> 01:11:13,431
Where did she get...

606
01:11:15,672 --> 01:11:16,866
A baby?

607
01:11:24,113 --> 01:11:27,105
Who knows?
Maybe I would have been good at it.

608
01:12:32,882 --> 01:12:34,543
Hey, Danny. Danny?

609
01:12:37,720 --> 01:12:41,053
I gotta tell you something. It's a secret.

610
01:12:42,892 --> 01:12:44,917
You want to hear a secret?

611
01:12:47,563 --> 01:12:49,497
- Sure.
- At the stadium,

612
01:12:54,904 --> 01:12:57,338
some of those people, they were...

613
01:12:59,675 --> 01:13:01,870
They were still alive, Danny.

614
01:13:04,580 --> 01:13:07,674
We were gonna dump them in the grave
and then...

615
01:13:09,285 --> 01:13:11,253
Some of them would move.

616
01:13:14,157 --> 01:13:16,182
I'd look at the supervisor,

617
01:13:18,194 --> 01:13:20,321
and he'd pretend not to see, so...

618
01:13:22,965 --> 01:13:25,297
So we'd pretend not to see them,

619
01:13:27,637 --> 01:13:29,002
but we did.

620
01:13:30,706 --> 01:13:33,106
We did, and we'd bury them anyway.

621
01:13:34,777 --> 01:13:38,042
- There were so many bodies, Danny.
- I know.

622
01:13:38,881 --> 01:13:41,145
- So many.
- I know.

623
01:13:44,187 --> 01:13:46,382
How the hell did we get here?

624
01:13:49,992 --> 01:13:53,484
- I don't know, Brian.
- You know.

625
01:13:56,165 --> 01:13:57,632
We both know.

626
01:13:59,602 --> 01:14:01,069
We both know.

627
01:14:03,673 --> 01:14:05,140
We both know.

628
01:14:06,809 --> 01:14:08,709
We both...

629
01:14:51,087 --> 01:14:52,987
Where you going, Danny?

630
01:14:59,729 --> 01:15:01,526
Where you going, man?

631
01:15:02,765 --> 01:15:04,562
We're leaving, Brian.

632
01:15:16,545 --> 01:15:19,537
- Come on.
- Come on, come on, come on, come on!

633
01:15:23,152 --> 01:15:25,848
- Shit!
- Oh, my God.

634
01:16:02,858 --> 01:16:04,849
I need those keys, Brian.

635
01:16:05,928 --> 01:16:07,020
Sure.

636
01:16:09,265 --> 01:16:10,926
And I need a ride.

637
01:16:13,636 --> 01:16:16,662
- You know I can't.
- Come on, Danny.

638
01:16:19,075 --> 01:16:23,136
The ocean, you and me, one more time.

639
01:16:24,981 --> 01:16:26,949
You remember how it was.

640
01:16:28,351 --> 01:16:31,946
Hitting those waves
before everything turned to shit.

641
01:16:33,489 --> 01:16:35,354
Just give me the keys.

642
01:16:37,193 --> 01:16:38,683
You want them?

643
01:16:39,862 --> 01:16:43,696
Shoot me or take me with you.

644
01:16:47,436 --> 01:16:51,338
- Brian, don't do it.
- I'm not gonna end up like them, Danny.

645
01:16:53,776 --> 01:16:56,176
Rotting alive, alone.

646
01:16:58,114 --> 01:17:00,912
You can't tell whether they're alive
or dead.

647
01:17:00,983 --> 01:17:03,451
Please, Brian. Don't.

648
01:17:06,889 --> 01:17:09,619
- It's what we decided.
- I'm dying, Danny!

649
01:17:12,762 --> 01:17:15,287
I don't give a fuck about the rules.

650
01:17:19,068 --> 01:17:20,558
You made them.

651
01:17:23,105 --> 01:17:24,766
My little brother.

652
01:17:26,909 --> 01:17:29,309
I taught him everything he knows.

653
01:18:25,034 --> 01:18:28,993
<i>I drive and wait for a storm to come</i>

654
01:18:30,739 --> 01:18:32,536
<i>and wash us all away,</i>

655
01:18:34,677 --> 01:18:36,201
<i>but it doesn't.</i>

656
01:18:41,584 --> 01:18:43,381
<i>It's a beautiful day.</i>

657
01:18:45,087 --> 01:18:47,612
<i>And it shouldn't be a beautiful day.</i>

658
01:18:51,060 --> 01:18:52,254
<i>I wait,</i>

659
01:18:54,830 --> 01:18:56,855
<i>but nothing happens to me.</i>

660
01:19:00,469 --> 01:19:05,338
<i>And for the first time,</i>
<i>I feel like I am alone in the world.</i>

661
01:19:20,823 --> 01:19:24,987
<i>We made it.</i>
<i>Two strangers with nothing left to say.</i>

662
01:19:30,499 --> 01:19:33,024
<i>Brian and I used to love this place,</i>

663
01:19:34,403 --> 01:19:36,837
<i>the hotel, the beach.</i>

664
01:19:41,677 --> 01:19:46,546
<i>They still look exactly the same,</i>
<i>but they're just places now.</i>

665
01:19:57,893 --> 01:19:59,952
<i>Brian! Danny! Come on!</i>

666
01:20:00,029 --> 01:20:02,429
<i>I don't know what'll happen next.</i>

667
01:20:03,499 --> 01:20:05,831
<i>I don't know how long I'll live.</i>

668
01:20:15,444 --> 01:20:17,537
<i>But I know I will be alone.</i>

